├── backend/
│   ├── app/
│   │   ├── api/          # API endpoints
│   │   ├── models/       # Database models
│   │   ├── schemas/      # Pydantic schemas
│   │   ├── services/     # Business logic
│   │   ├── utils/        # Utilities
│   │   └── db/           # Database configuration
│   ├── requirements.txt
│   ├── .env.example
│   └── run.py
├── frontend/
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── components/   # React components
│   │   ├── pages/        # Page components
│   │   ├── services/     # API services
│   │   ├── store/        # State management
│   │   └── utils/        # Utilities
│   ├── package.json
│   └── .env.example
└── README.md
```

## 🔄 Bulk Upload Templates

Download CSV templates from the Bulk Upload page:

### Properties Template
```csv
name,address,type,total_units
Sunset Apartments,123 Main St,apartment,10
```

### Units Template
```csv
property_name,unit_number,bedrooms,bathrooms,rent_amount,status
Sunset Apartments,A101,2,1,25000,vacant
```

### Tenants Template
```csv
property_name,unit_number,full_name,phone,email,id_number,base_rent,security_deposit_amount,move_in_date
Sunset Apartments,A101,John Doe,+254722123456,john@email.com,12345678,25000,25000,2024-01-01
```

## 🚀 Deployment

### Backend (e.g., Railway, Render, DigitalOcean)

1. Set environment variables
2. Run database migrations
3. Deploy using Gunicorn:
   ```bash
   gunicorn app.main:app -w 4 -k uvicorn.workers.UvicornWorker
   ```

### Frontend (e.g., Vercel, Netlify, Cloudflare Pages)

1. Build the project:
   ```bash
   npm run build
   ```
2. Deploy the `dist` folder

### Environment Variables

Make sure to set all required environment variables in your deployment platform.

